INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26709, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You returned. This is good. The Stone Lords have been asking after you.', 26365), -- The Stone Throne
(26971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maruut said when all dis started dat he would gladly give his life ta see our task done. He would be proud of dis success... of dis death.$B$BDa rift be closed on dis side. Deepholm should calm down a bit. It\'ll be takin\' time for Thrall to mend da wound in Azeroth, and we\'ll be needin\' to remain until he finishes.$B$BThank you for all ya\'ve done. I don\'t tink we could have been accomplishin\' dis so soon without you.', 26365), -- The Binding
(26875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight forces continue to stream in, but it looks like the Earthen Ring defenders can handle them.', 26365), -- Undying Twilight
(26833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorsik has arrived. All of the pieces of the World Pillar are here, thanks to you.$B$BWhat you have done for us is immeasurable.  These final moments shall be the most crucial.  I hesitate to ask more of you, but I\'d like you to stay with us and see this through.$B$BThe Twilight\'s Hammer was devastated by your attacks, but not destroyed.  It\'s no stretch to assume they will try to stop us from completing our ritual.\n', 26365), -- Word In Stone
(26832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let Lorthuna escape? I warned you of this.$B$BStill, their forces are shattered and their resources cut off. There is little they can do to me or my allies.', 26365), -- Therazane's Mercy
(26829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their blood upon the earth is a sweet thing. I shall cherish every moment, slowly extinguishing the stragglers from my realm.', 26365), -- The Stone March
(26831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you were here. I find my size to be inhibiting when it comes to dragon riding, strangely.', 26365), -- The Twilight Flight
(26828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so you arrive, fleshling.  As promised.', 26365), -- Our Part of the Bargain
(26827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what I thought not possible. Quite impressive, $c.', 26365), -- Rallying the Earthen Ring
(26752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya\'ve done well, $Gbrotha:sista;. Da Stonemother be listenin\' and da World Pillar is not far from our reach.', 26365), -- Audience with the Stonemother
(26750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'ve come.$B$BFleshlings just like you killed my daughter... my only daughter. With no provocation.$B$BNot sated at stripping me of my family, more of you flocked to Deathwing to serve him in ravaging my home.$B$BYou\'re quite arrogant to come before me asking for MY help. I\'m tempted to crush you where you stand.', 26365), -- At the Stonemother's Call
(26585, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So your words prove true. You have my gratitude, $r.', 26365), -- Corruption Destruction
(26584, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done fleshling. Your presence complemented my brothers well.', 26365), -- Shaken and Stirred
(26583, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r.$B$BGorsik shall hear of your deed. Therazane shall hear of your deed.$B$BYou are quite vicious for one so small... and so soft.', 26365), -- Wrath of the Fungalmancer
(26579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You carry with you a certain degree of potency. I can find some respect for such strength, especially in your kind.$B$BMy concerns are not yet abated. Not for the source of the overgrowth, and not for you.', 26365), -- Gone Soft
(26582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The stone troggs? And I am to trust you at your word?$B$BI have no love for the Verlok anyway. Suspicion is more than enough reason to lay waste to them. We shall see if your word is true.', 26365), -- Unnatural Causes
(26578, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have appealed to Diamant. He is patient. Trusting. Perhaps too much so. You have much to prove if you wish my favor, $r.$B$BStill, this is a start.', 26365), -- Doomshrooms
(26581, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let the mist touch your skin? I hope there weren\'t any adverse affects.', 26365), -- A Head Full of Wind
(26580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you again, $g brother:sister;. I see that your efforts go well. The Stone Lords appear to be showing you some degree of trust.$B$BWe\'ve come to help. We might be of some aid in tracking down the source of this sudden growth. I highly suspect your giant friend\'s aggressions are focused in the wrong direction.', 26365), -- Familiar Intruders
(26577, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are Diamant\'s chosen.$B$BSo small. So fragile.$B$BDo you realize that your actions shall be the basis by which your entire, \"Earthen Ring\" is judged? You truly think you can stand for so many?$B$BYou are a fool. A confident fool. We shall see if you are a capable fool as well.', 26365), -- Rocky Upheaval
(26259, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is still great power present in his blood, $n.  I can sense it even now.$B$BYet there is also much corruption.  I am not sure we can salvage the Earthwarder\'s essence from this.', 26365), -- Blood of the Earthwarder
(26876, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts in repairing the World Pillar are invaluable, $n.  Once the Temple of Earth\'s structure is stable again, the rift between the worlds will begin to stabilize.', 26365), -- The World Pillar Fragment
(26861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  When we make our move against Abyssion, we should be able to do so without reinforcements coming to his aid.', 26365), -- Block the Gates
(26857, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That ought to get the dragon\'s attention, $n.', 26365), -- Abyssion's Minions
(26771, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  Here\'s to hoping the trap performs as well when we try it on Abyssion.', 26365), -- Testing the Trap
(26766, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be enough to lure the beast, $n.', 26365), -- Big Game, Big Bait
(26768, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see if the snare can ground something larger than a drake.', 26365), -- To Catch a Dragon
(27061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So we\'re going to have to take on Abyssion to get the fragment?  This operation just got a whole lot more difficult all of a sudden.', 26365), -- The Twilight Overlook
(27010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have the information we need.  Let\'s not tip our hand by engaging the enemy too soon.', 26365), -- Quicksilver Submersion
(27007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the place.  Our scouts confirmed the presence of high-ranking Twilight officers nearby as well as potential trogg hunting parties.$B$BBe on the lookout, $n.', 26365), -- Silvermarsh Rendezvous
(26260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is an entry for an upcoming meeting at the Upper Silvermarsh.$B$BThis must be where the Forgemaster is.', 26365), -- The Forgemaster's Log
(26261, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us find this journal.  We\'re getting close to the World Pillar fragment, I can sense it.', 26365), -- Question the Slaves
(26256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re keeping slaves here?  We ought to free them regardless, but perhaps they might also aid us in finding the forgemaster.', 26365), -- Bleed the Bloodshaper
(26258, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This must be where the world pillar fragment was brought.  Let\'s have a closer look.', 26365), -- Deathwing's Fall
(26255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must investigate your findings further, but we must not lose track of the fragment.', 26365), -- Return to the Temple of Earth
(26427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All right, help me get tied to the wheel.$B$B<Moody sips from the bottle.>', 26365), -- Without a Captain or Crew
(26254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have our answers, $n.  Let\'s report back.', 26365), -- Some Spraining to Do
(26250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi, this was a heavy one!  He nearly broke me gryphon\'s back!$B$BAre you ready to interrogate the ogre, $n?', 26365), -- On Second Thought, Take One Prisoner
(26251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  The Twilight\'s Hammer is an evil that we must fight anywhere we find them.', 26365), -- Take No Prisoners
(26248, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were bound to run into the Twilight\'s Hammer sooner or later, $n.  If they\'re behind this, it\'s quite likely that the World Pillar fragment is in their possession.', 26365), -- All Our Friends Are Dead
(26249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ship is filled with rats...', 26365), -- The Admiral's Cabin
(26247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi, $n!  I was told I\'d have company soon.', 26365), -- Diplomacy First
(27042, 4, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the ol\' spirit! One less nasty in this world that the little ones will have ta worry about when they go ta sleep at night.$B$BNot ta mention that we won\'t have ta be worrying about him none no more neither!$B$BNow let\'s see here. I think we have somethin\' in our crates that\'ll make a fittin\' reward fer ya.', 26365), -- Fight Fire and Water and Air with...
(27058, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! You found out what the Twilight\'s Hammer were up to and you stopped them dead in their tracks!$B$B<Mowi gets up on her tippy toes and gives you a kiss on the cheek.>$B$BNow I\'m certain that I have something around here for you.$B$B<She begins rummaging around for your reward.>', 26365), -- The Wrong Sequence
(26792, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. We\'ve never had such a problem in Deepholm before the destruction of the World Pillar.$B$BYour Earthen Ring must repair the damage before it\'s too late.', 26365), -- Fungal Monstrosities
(26791, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They won\'t have any more of those fungal giants to throw against us!', 26365), -- Sprout No More
(26834, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $n. Now we\'ll get somewhere.', 26365), -- Down Into the Chasm
(26770, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A few less stone troggs is always a good thing. Glad to see that you\'re a decent $c after all.$B$BWe\'ll soon know the exact location where they\'re keeping my father captive. Hope you survive until then.', 26365), -- Mystic Masters
(26762, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a nice bit of work, $n.$B$BWith our constructs back up and running behind their main lines, it\'s only a matter of time now before we make the big push through and rescue the Stonefather.', 26365), -- Reactivate the Constructs
(26755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a great start, $n, but we\'re going to need you to fly over into the town and stir up some trouble.', 26365), -- Keep Them off the Front
(26632, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The catapult chief gives you an appraising look.>$B$BWord of your prowess has spread ahead of you, $r. Let\'s see if you can help us keep these fungal horrors off of the front.', 26365), -- Close Escort
(27126, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t thank you enough, $c. Now, let\'s see if we can get this catapult moving again.', 26365), -- Rush Delivery
(26625, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Gravel solemnly nods his head.>$B$BFinally, we can move forward and rescue the Stonefather.', 26365), -- Troggzor the Earthinator
(26591, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you ever get tired of your being a $c, come look me up. You seem very good with those fleshy hands of yours.', 26365), -- Battlefront Triage
(26537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a good dent, but it\'s clear to me that we\'re going to have to handle this a slightly different way.', 26365), -- Shatter Them!
(26564, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then. Maybe you\'re okay after all.$B$BAlright, alright... don\'t get all bent out of shape. Just give me a few moments with these parts.', 26365), -- Fixer Upper
(26502, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Clay grumbles to himself.>$B$BThose\'ll do. Just put them down over there.$B$B<The Earthen looks you up and down with one eye and then spits dust onto the ground.>$B$BI\'m going to have something for you to do in a moment. Maybe.', 26365), -- Thunder Stones
(26501, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good. We no longer need to worry about stone trogg attacks from the rear.$B$BLet\'s see what you can do for us on the front.', 26365), -- Sealing the Way
(26499, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, $n. You\'ve made all the difference, and the fate of these cowardly stone trogg ambushers is set in stone.$B$BNow we must get about the business of retaking Stonehearth.', 26365), -- Stonefather's Boon
(26500, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a bad start, though you\'ll have to destroy more of them than that if you\'re going to rescue the Stonefather.$B$BA lot more.', 26365), -- We're Surrounded
(27935, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what few others could have. Defeating Avalanchion was no small feat.$B$BI\'m impressed, $n. Will you help us with our war against the stone troggs so that we can rescue the Stonefather?', 26365), -- Bring Down the Avalanche
(27934, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that the ritual is complete and you are near Avalanchion, there\'s only one thing left to do.', 26365), -- One With the Ground
(27933, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should do. I\'ll just need a moment to prepare the ritual.', 26365), -- Elemental Ore
(27932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Without all of their giants, Therazane\'s forces will have a harder time taking Stonehearth.$B$BNow, if you please, hand back the axe. I\'ll keep it safe until you can rescue the Stonefather.', 26365), -- The Axe of Earthly Sundering
(27931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $r, you\'re here.$B$BWe\'ll have to act fast if we\'re to prevent Therazane\'s forces from attacking.', 26365), -- The Quaking Fields
(26484, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Stonefather\'s son, Flint, sent you? No time to talk.$B$BWe must prevent a second front from opening up on the war!', 26365), -- To Stonehearth's Aid
(27040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah ha! So, that\'s it! They\'re planning on invading Uldum.$B$BWhat\'s worse is that the pyramid inside the Maker\'s Rise at Uldum can be reconfigured to become a weapon. A weapon that is capable of destroying all life on Azeroth!', 26365), -- Decryption Made Easy
(27006, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A waygate?! The culties dug up a Titan waygate?', 26365), -- Fly Over
(27004, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Mowi takes a look at the plans that you hand to her.>$B$BBut... but, this is just gibberish!$B$BWhat does this even say? What language is that?', 26365), -- The Twilight Plot
(27136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  We need all the power we can muster to keep Deepholm stable.', 26365), -- Elemental Energy
(26246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why would the Alliance attack the Horde just as they\'re about to deliver a fragment of the World Pillar to us?', 26365), -- Captain's Log
(26245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The clues point to an obvious conclusion.  Too obvious perhaps.', 26365), -- Gunship Down
(26413, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are honored by Flint Oremantle\'s presence. I am given to understand that the Stonefather is in possession of a fragment of the World Pillar.$B$BIt is imperative that we recover all of the fragments. The instability between worlds is increasing. Soon it may become too great even for mighty Thrall to hold at bay.', 26365), -- Take Him to the Earthcaller
(26411, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like that did it. He should come to any moment now.$B$BI told you I was a grand master of alchemy!$B$BI\'ve got some extra resin leftover. I can make it into all kinds of explosively wonderful stuff. What do you want?', 26365), -- Apply and Flash Dry
(27135, 430, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh oh. Sounds like he wasn\'t very happy about the situation. How was I to know? I\'m just an initiate after all.$B$BAnyway, I\'ll worry about Magmatooth later.', 26365); -- Something that Burns
